001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.tab;
002
003import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.base.AbstractComponentService;
004import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.base.ComponentType;
005import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.button.ButtonComponentType;
006import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.factory.ComponentFactory;
007import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.selenium.smart.SmartWebDriver;
008import io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.selenium.smart.SmartWebElement;
009import org.openqa.selenium.By;
010
011/**
012 * Implementation of the {@link TabService} interface, offering functionality for tab
013 * interactions such as clicking, verifying if tabs are enabled, visible, or selected.
014 * Extends {@link AbstractComponentService} to manage creation and retrieval of
015 * {@link Tab} instances.
016 *
017 * <p>This class references {@link TabComponentType} to determine the specific tab component,
018 * ensuring consistent handling of tab-based elements across different UI designs.
019 *
020 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
021 */
022public class TabServiceImpl extends AbstractComponentService<TabComponentType, Tab> implements TabService {
023
024   /**
025    * Constructs a new {@code TabServiceImpl} with the given {@link SmartWebDriver}.
026    *
027    * @param driver the smart web driver used to interact with browser elements.
028    */
029   public TabServiceImpl(SmartWebDriver driver) {
030      super(driver);
031   }
032
033   /**
034    * Creates a new {@link Tab} component for the specified {@link TabComponentType}.
035    *
036    * @param componentType the tab component type.
037    * @return a new or existing {@link Tab} instance.
038    */
039   @Override
040   protected Tab createComponent(final TabComponentType componentType) {
041      return ComponentFactory.getTabComponent(componentType, driver);
042   }
043
044   /**
045    * Clicks a tab, identified by text, within the specified container.
046    *
047    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
048    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
049    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
050    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
051    */
052   @Override
053   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> void click(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container,
054                                                     final String tabText) {
055      tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).click(container, tabText);
056   }
057
058   /**
059    * Clicks a tab within a specified container, without referring to the tab text.
060    *
061    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
062    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
063    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
064    */
065   @Override
066   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> void click(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container) {
067      tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).click(container);
068   }
069
070   /**
071    * Clicks a tab identified by text, without referencing a container.
072    *
073    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
074    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
075    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
076    */
077   @Override
078   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> void click(final T componentType, final String tabText) {
079      tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).click(tabText);
080   }
081
082   /**
083    * Clicks a tab identified by a locator.
084    *
085    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
086    * @param tabLocator    the locator for the tab.
087    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
088    */
089   @Override
090   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> void click(final T componentType, final By tabLocator) {
091      tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).click(tabLocator);
092   }
093
094   /**
095    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is enabled within a specified container.
096    *
097    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
098    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
099    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
100    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
101    * @return true if the tab is enabled, otherwise false.
102    */
103   @Override
104   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isEnabled(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container,
105                                                            final String tabText) {
106      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isEnabled(container, tabText);
107   }
108
109   /**
110    * Checks if a tab is enabled within a specified container, without referring to tab text.
111    *
112    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
113    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
114    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
115    * @return true if the tab is enabled, otherwise false.
116    */
117   @Override
118   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isEnabled(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container) {
119      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isEnabled(container);
120   }
121
122   /**
123    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is enabled without referencing a container.
124    *
125    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
126    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
127    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
128    * @return true if the tab is enabled, otherwise false.
129    */
130   @Override
131   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isEnabled(final T componentType, final String tabText) {
132      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isEnabled(tabText);
133   }
134
135   /**
136    * Checks if a tab, identified by a locator, is enabled.
137    *
138    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
139    * @param tabLocator    the locator for the tab.
140    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
141    * @return true if the tab is enabled, otherwise false.
142    */
143   @Override
144   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isEnabled(final T componentType, final By tabLocator) {
145      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isEnabled(tabLocator);
146   }
147
148   /**
149    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is visible within a specified container.
150    *
151    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
152    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
153    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
154    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
155    * @return true if the tab is visible, otherwise false.
156    */
157   @Override
158   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isVisible(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container,
159                                                            final String tabText) {
160      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isVisible(container, tabText);
161   }
162
163   /**
164    * Checks if a tab is visible within a specified container, without referencing tab text.
165    *
166    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
167    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
168    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
169    * @return true if the tab is visible, otherwise false.
170    */
171   @Override
172   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isVisible(final T componentType, final SmartWebElement container) {
173      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isVisible(container);
174   }
175
176   /**
177    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is visible without referencing a container.
178    *
179    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
180    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
181    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
182    * @return true if the tab is visible, otherwise false.
183    */
184   @Override
185   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isVisible(final T componentType, final String tabText) {
186      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isVisible(tabText);
187   }
188
189   /**
190    * Checks if a tab, identified by a locator, is visible.
191    *
192    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
193    * @param tabLocator    the locator for the tab.
194    * @param <T>           a type extending {@link ButtonComponentType}.
195    * @return true if the tab is visible, otherwise false.
196    */
197   @Override
198   public <T extends ButtonComponentType> boolean isVisible(final T componentType, final By tabLocator) {
199      return tabComponent((TabComponentType) componentType).isVisible(tabLocator);
200   }
201
202   /**
203    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is selected within the specified container.
204    *
205    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
206    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
207    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
208    * @return true if the tab is selected, otherwise false.
209    */
210   @Override
211   public boolean isSelected(final TabComponentType componentType, final SmartWebElement container,
212                             final String tabText) {
213      return tabComponent(componentType).isSelected(container, tabText);
214   }
215
216   /**
217    * Checks if a tab is selected within the specified container, without referring to tab text.
218    *
219    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
220    * @param container     the container element holding the tab.
221    * @return true if the tab is selected, otherwise false.
222    */
223   @Override
224   public boolean isSelected(final TabComponentType componentType, final SmartWebElement container) {
225      return tabComponent(componentType).isSelected(container);
226   }
227
228   /**
229    * Checks if a tab, identified by text, is selected without referencing a container.
230    *
231    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
232    * @param tabText       the text identifying the tab.
233    * @return true if the tab is selected, otherwise false.
234    */
235   @Override
236   public boolean isSelected(final TabComponentType componentType, final String tabText) {
237      return tabComponent(componentType).isSelected(tabText);
238   }
239
240   /**
241    * Checks if a tab, identified by a locator, is selected.
242    *
243    * @param componentType the type of the tab component.
244    * @param tabLocator    the locator for the tab.
245    * @return true if the tab is selected, otherwise false.
246    */
247   @Override
248   public boolean isSelected(final TabComponentType componentType, final By tabLocator) {
249      return tabComponent(componentType).isSelected(tabLocator);
250   }
251
252   /**
253    * Performs a table insertion action by clicking a tab within a cell element.
254    *
255    * @param cellElement   the table cell element containing the tab.
256    * @param componentType the component type, expected to be a {@link TabComponentType}.
257    * @param values        additional values (currently unused).
258    */
259   @Override
260   public void tableInsertion(final SmartWebElement cellElement, final ComponentType componentType,
261                              final String... values) {
262      if (!(componentType instanceof TabComponentType tabType)) {
263         throw new IllegalArgumentException("Component type needs to be from: TabComponentType.");
264      }
265      tabComponent(tabType).clickElementInCell(cellElement);
266   }
267
268   /**
269    * Retrieves the {@link Tab} component for the specified {@link TabComponentType}.
270    *
271    * @param componentType the tab component type.
272    * @return a {@link Tab} instance for managing tab interactions.
273    */
274   private Tab tabComponent(final TabComponentType componentType) {
275      return getOrCreateComponent(componentType);
276   }
277
278}
